00:00:02.160 --> 00:00:07.290
Here, 
my "White chocolate pudding with MACCHA sauce" is ready.

00:00:07.330 --> 00:00:11.040
It takes very little time to make.
Try it for yourself.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.020
Hello, there.

00:00:14.060 --> 00:00:18.590
Now, I'm going to make 
"White chocolate pudding with MACCHA sauce" .

00:00:18.630 --> 00:00:23.420
By adding a white chocolate,
the pudding becomes very rich and delicious. 

00:00:23.460 --> 00:00:25.670
So, I introduce the ingredients.

00:00:25.700 --> 00:00:30.710
White chocolate bar, Milk, Cornstarch, Sugar.

00:00:30.740 --> 00:00:33.470
Here are for MACCHA sacue (Green tea sauce).

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:37.260
MACCHA (green powdered tea), Sugar, Cornstarch.

00:00:37.290 --> 00:00:39.450
So, let's get started.

00:00:39.490 --> 00:00:41.650
Now let's Get Started.

00:00:41.680 --> 00:00:47.410
First,
Heat half of the Milk (2/5 U.S.cup; 100ml).

00:00:47.440 --> 00:00:51.730
Turn on heat.

00:00:52.050 --> 00:00:56.750
Add a half bar of White chocolate.

00:00:58.610 --> 00:01:04.940
Add 1 tbsp Sugar.

00:01:06.570 --> 00:01:12.860
Melt the Sugar and Chocolate over at body temperature.

00:01:12.890 --> 00:01:16.690
Oh, smell delicious.

00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:29.100
When they have all melted,
add 2 tbsp Cornstarch to the remaining Milk.

00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:33.820
Star and melt the Cornstarch.

00:01:35.430 --> 00:01:41.270
Add the liquid to the pan.

00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:45.300
And, stir the liquid constantly until it has thickened.

00:01:45.330 --> 00:01:52.920
Look, it has thickened like this.
Remove from the heat.

00:01:53.510 --> 00:01:59.130
And, stir the sauce again until well-blended.

00:01:59.930 --> 00:02:01.960
Good!

00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:05.640
When it comes to be like this,

00:02:07.790 --> 00:02:14.450
Move to a cup quickly.

00:02:21.110 --> 00:02:24.890
Here, The White chocolate pudding is done.
It's just too easy, isn't it?!

00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:28.210
Next, 
make the MACCHA sauce (Green tea sauce).

00:02:28.240 --> 00:02:34.260
First,
Mix the all ingredients for the MACCHA sauce.

00:02:34.970 --> 00:02:38.410
1 tsp Sugar.

00:02:38.450 --> 00:02:42.230
1 tsp Cornstarch.

00:02:42.260 --> 00:02:46.740
1 tbsp MACCHA (green powdered tea).

00:02:47.210 --> 00:02:54.090
And, 1/5 U.S.cup Water (50ml).

00:02:58.340 --> 00:03:01.050
When the all ingredients have melted,

00:03:01.150 --> 00:03:06.970
Move to a pan.

00:03:07.010 --> 00:03:12.550
Turn on the heat.

00:03:12.590 --> 00:03:15.930
Heat the liquid until it has thickened.

00:03:15.960 --> 00:03:18.880
The sauce is being thickened little by little.

00:03:18.920 --> 00:03:20.950
Heat a little more.

00:03:20.980 --> 00:03:23.690
Good! The sauce has good thickness.

00:03:23.730 --> 00:03:30.160
Turn off the heat and pour to the cup.

00:03:39.230 --> 00:03:41.910
The pudding is done.

00:03:41.950 --> 00:03:46.630
After this,
cover plastic wrap and chill for 1 hour in the refrigerator.

00:03:47.230 --> 00:03:50.800
Cover the cup with a plastic wrap.

00:03:55.180 --> 00:03:59.360
Chill it for 1 hour in the refrigerator.

00:03:59.390 --> 00:04:01.280
1 hour has passed.

00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:03.990
Let me have a look.

00:04:04.020 --> 00:04:07.560
Open the wrap.

00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:10.580
Oh good! They have solidified.

00:04:10.610 --> 00:04:16.250
Finally,
Put toppings that you want.

00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:20.020
Today,
I top with gold powder.

00:04:24.030 --> 00:04:31.170
Here,
It's ready to be served.

00:04:31.210 --> 00:04:36.030
And there,
my "White chocolate pudding with MACCHA sauce" is ready.

00:04:36.060 --> 00:04:40.130
It takes very little time to make.
Try it for yourself.

